> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning — Common Pitfalls:**
> 1. **Calling `wait()` / `notify()` outside synchronized block** — instantly throws `IllegalMonitorStateException`. Lose **2 marks**.
> 2. **Using `if` instead of `while`** for the condition check around `wait()` — misses **spurious wakeup handling**. Lose **1 mark**.
> 3. **Confusing `sleep()` with `wait()`** — `sleep()` does **NOT** release the lock. Examiners deduct marks if you misuse it for inter-thread communication.
> 4. **Forgetting to call `notify()` / `notifyAll()`** — leads to **deadlock** in Producer-Consumer. Use `notifyAll()` for safety (single-buffer pattern).
> 5. **Synchronizing on wrong object** — using `synchronized(this)` inside a static method where there is no `this`. Use `ClassName.class` instead.

---

### 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **High-Density Revision Checklist:**

- **Definition**: Synchronization = mutual exclusion of critical sections using intrinsic locks.
- **`synchronized` keyword**: applied to methods (lock on `this` / `Class`) or blocks (explicit lock object).
- **Monitor components**: Lock (mutex) + Entry Set + Wait Set.
- **Race Condition**: arises when read-check-update is non-atomic → fixed by `synchronized`.
- **`wait()` releases lock; `sleep()` does NOT release lock.**
- **`wait()`, `notify()`, `notifyAll()` must be inside `synchronized`** else `IllegalMonitorStateException`.
- **Always use `while` (not `if)** around `wait()` to handle spurious wakeups.
- **`notify()` wakes one thread; `notifyAll()` wakes all** — prefer `notifyAll()` for safety.
- **Deadlock prevention**: Lock ordering + timeout via `tryLock()`.
- **Static synchronized method**: locks on `ClassName.class`, not `this`.
- **Happens-before guarantee**: `synchronized` ensures memory visibility across threads via memory barriers.
- **Preferred modern alternative**: `java.util.concurrent.locks.ReentrantLock` for advanced features (fairness, tryLock, interruptibility).
- **Lab Viva Point**: Be ready to draw the monitor's Entry Set, Owner, and Wait Set on paper.
- **Lab Viva Point**: Explain the difference between **intrinsic lock** (every object) and **explicit lock** (`ReentrantLock`).
- **Compiler hint**: `synchronized` on a method is shorthand for wrapping the entire method body in `synchronized(this) { ... }`.

